  "content": "# Implementation Plan: PDF Upload, Extraction, and Combined HTML Export Tool\n\n## Objective\n\nBuild a local application with React frontend and Python (FastAPI) backend that allows users to upload PDF files, extracts text from all PDFs in `/sourcedocs`, combines the extracted text into a single timestamped HTML file in `/destination`, and provides UI feedback.\n\n## Architecture Overview\n\n- **Frontend**: React + TypeScript application providing file upload UI, progress indicators, and result display.\n- **Backend**: Python FastAPI service handling file uploads, PDF text extraction, HTML generation, and file management.\n- **Filesystem**: Two primary directories: `/sourcedocs` (uploaded PDFs) and `/destination` (generated HTML files).\n\n## Steps\n\n### Step 1: Project Setup and Structure\n1. Create project root directory with recommended structure.\n2. Initialize backend Python project with `requirements.txt` and virtual environment.\n3. Initialize frontend React project with TypeScript template.\n4. Create necessary directories (`/sourcedocs`, `/destination`) if they don't exist.\n\n### Step 2: Backend Core Setup\n1. Implement FastAPI application with CORS middleware for frontend communication.\n2. Create file service module for handling file operations (save, list, validate PDF).\n3. Implement PDF text extraction module using `pdfplumber` (fallback to `pypdf`).\n4. Create HTML generation module for combining extracted text into a well-formatted HTML document.\n5. Implement timestamp generation for output filenames (format: `combined_YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS.html`).\n\n### Step 3: Backend API Endpoints\n1. `POST /upload`: Accept multiple PDF files, validate, and save to `/sourcedocs`.\n2. `GET /files`: List existing PDF files in `/sourcedocs`.\n3. `POST /process`: Trigger extraction process on all PDFs in `/sourcedocs`, generate combined HTML, save to `/destination`, return result metadata.\n4. `GET /results`: List previously generated HTML files in `/destination`.\n\n### Step 4: Frontend UI Components\n1. Create file upload component with drag-and-drop and multi-file selection.\n2. Implement file list component showing uploaded PDFs with status.\n3. Build process control component with \"Upload & Process\" button.\n4. Create status display component for showing progress and errors.\n5. Implement result display component showing generated HTML file path and download link.\n\n### Step 5: Frontend-Backend Integration\n1. Configure Axios for API communication.\n2. Connect upload component to `/upload` endpoint with progress tracking.\n3. Connect process button to `/process` endpoint with loading states.\n4. Fetch and display results from `/results` endpoint.\n\n### Step 6: Processing Logic\n1. Implement deterministic processing order: sort PDFs by filename ascending (case-insensitive).\n2. Handle extraction errors gracefully (continue processing other files, log errors).\n3. Preserve page boundaries in combined output with clear separation between PDFs.\n4. Generate HTML with simple, readable styling (headers for each PDF, page markers, timestamps).\n\n### Step 7: Error Handling and Validation\n1. Backend: Validate file type (PDF), size limits, and file integrity.\n2. Frontend: Client-side validation before upload.\n3. Comprehensive error reporting to UI for failed uploads, extraction failures, etc.\n4. Logging for debugging (file operations, extraction results, errors).\n\n### Step 8: Testing\n1. Backend unit tests for extraction, HTML generation, and file operations.\n2. API integration tests using FastAPI TestClient.\n3. Frontend component tests with React Testing Library.\n4. End-to-end workflow test (upload → process → verify output).\n\n### Step 9: Documentation and Run Instructions\n1. Create README with setup instructions for both backend and frontend.\n2. Document environment variables (if any) and configuration options.\n3. Provide example usage.\n\n## Files to Create/Modify\n\n### Backend (`/backend/`)\n- `app.py` - FastAPI application and endpoints\n- `file_service.py` - File operations, directo… [6656 chars total]"
